  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nIf you create a repository index without passing the `--url` flag, your index will point to relative paths for the chart tarballs.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nentries:\r\n  alpine:\r\n  - created: 2016-11-18T15:05:51.078570269-07:00\r\n    ...\r\n    name: alpine\r\n    urls:\r\n    - alpine-0.3.0.tgz\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis repository can be added but nor fetch nor install work.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ helm repo add tscharts https://technosophos.github.com/tscharts\r\n\"tscharts\" has been added to your repositories\r\n\r\n$ helm search alpine\r\nNAME           \tVERSION\tDESCRIPTION                    \r\ntscharts/alpine\t0.3.0  \tDeploy a basic Alpine Linux pod\r\n\r\n$ helm install tscharts/alpine\r\nError: file \"tscharts/alpine\" not found\r\n\r\n$ helm fetch tscharts/alpine\r\nError: Get alpine-0.3.0.tgz: unsupported protocol scheme \"\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems to be a common/known issue [1] and https://github.com/kubernetes/helm/issues/2315.\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, Helm should be able to compose the chart url by using on the URL provided (which is required) during the `helm repo add` command. I remember this behavior so we might have added a regression.\r\n\r\nIf we do not do this, at least we should make `helm repo index` `--url` flag in mandatory and validate the repository index during `helm repo add`.\r\n\r\n[1] https://github.com/kubernetes/helm/blob/master/docs/chart_repository_faq.md#fetching",
